    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-07-05T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-07-05T02:00:00-05:00" n="409"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d409">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.796/7–544: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-07-05T10:00:00+03:00"
                            >July 5, 1944—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 1:42 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2422. Department’s 1533, June 22, 9 p.m. At my request the British Embassy is
                    sending to the Soviet Foreign Office a further note in which our views on the
                    “draft outline of an international convention and international authority for
                    its administration” are clearly set forth. In fact, substantially the same
                    language as given in the Department’s telegram under reference is used.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
